<br>
My feelings on the old rules are mixed. I liked the concept of alignments, however they were fatally flawed. All creatures capable of sentient thought are able to choose any path of morals in reality. So why restrict alignments for races? Classes I can understand, though I would plead for neutral necromancers, as the path of necromancy just involves a fascination with death, not with evil. If you wish for true roleplaying, then a choice should be allowed.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I would wish they would open all classes and gods to all races. Any circumstance is possible in theory. Again, if you wish for a true RPing experience, then allow all the possible paths! If you did that, sure a lot of people would play, say, gnome monks, but it doesn't mattter. If they roleplayed, and if any of us got more entertainment and roleplaying freedom out of it, then its fine. How much more interesting would it be to play a High elf warrior then an ogre warrior? A dark elf paladin? An ogre mage? Much. <br>
<br>
But listen. A lot of people diss the 'antihero' or 'renegade' path of roleplaying. It's not fair. So its been done before. So? What's your point? All your character archetypes have been done too. In great amounts. And thery can get just as old. We're all just recycled, slightly altered cliches. An archetype is by nature a cliche. So stop being down on us renegades. Seriously. It's far more interesting to have been born into evil and renounced it then to have been a goody goody all your life. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blaysethunderwraith>Blayse Thunderwraith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/28/03 11:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3840.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ha! Overdone renegade thing? So are all of our chars.</span><hr size=1> ((ooc.... have you ever TRIED being so straight and narrow all the time that you look like a straw? LOL  Try it sometime, friend, it ain't as easy as it seems.  You think that the evils get hacked on **laughs** try being such a goody goody that helps anyone of good ALL the time, half the time not hunting for yourself.... THAT is hard hehehehe and Gods it's fun when I hit my other server just to be a sneaky little wench)) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=villagereaver>villagereaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/30/03 8:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3840.topic&index=39>Reply</a>  